in: 0 0 1em 0;">On Wednesday June 27, 2017, the day before Ukraine&#8217;s =
Constitution Day, hospitals, banks, ATMs, power plants, the government, and=
 practically all businesses in the country were hit, seemingly simultaneous=
ly, with what appeared to be ransomware. It locked computers, deleted files=
, and spread at breakneck speed from computer to computer, and company to c=
ompany. Messing with Ukraine on its Constitution Day had become a Russian h=
acker pastime -- Ukraine&#8217;s neighbor routinely shut off the power or d=
eleted files -- but this was different, more vicious. It was also harder to=
